description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Membership and Finance Support Officer at NHS Benchmarking Network.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are seeking a motivated and conscientious individual to support the membership management, event administration and finance processes for the NHS Benchmarking Network. &lt;br /&gt;As the primary point of contact for membership queries, you will play a vital role in the continued success of the Network. You will support the administration of our growing offer of virtual events with opportunities to use your customer service skills to engage with our target audiences and the chance to contribute to innovation in this developing area. &lt;br /&gt;Working with the finance manager, you will support the finance processes related to the membership and be responsible for membership records. Working in a fast paced environment, you will apply excellent attention to detail to ensure accurate logging and follow up of member interactions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Benchmark Management Consulting runs the NHS Benchmarking Network, a member organisation that develops and delivers national benchmarking and data analytics projects for the NHS. As the leading benchmarking network for health and social care intelligence in the UK, we are proud to support our clients to improve NHS services and deliver the NHS Long Term Plan. In addition to a core annual work programme for members, we also undertake projects and audits commissioned by central NHS bodies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• educated to degree level, numerate with a good standard of written English&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• able to demonstrate excellent organisational skills, accuracy and attention to detail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• a confident user of Microsoft Office&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• able to demonstrate strong customer service skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• a strong team player&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• self-motivated, able to operate independently and willing to learn&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• flexible, adaptable and able to work under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
